The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, August 06, 2004 				 CPM to pile heat and pat
 A STAFF REPORTERCalcutta, Aug. 5: The CPM will fight the anti-people policies of the Congress-led United Progressive Alliance government at the Centre and, at the same time, ensure it survives the five-year term.																								We are now playing a dual role of coordination and confrontation. If necessary, we will fight the UPA government for its failure to implement the common minimum programme but we will also initiate measures to enable the government to last five years, CPM state secretary and politburo member Anil Biswas said today. 																								He was addressing a party programme to mark the 116th birth anniversary of Muzaffar Ahmed. 																								Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee, Lok Sabha Speaker Somnath Chatterjee and Jyoti Basu were present when Biswas spelt out the confrontation-and-coordination policy. 																								Biswas also said: We are fighting them (the Congress) for the past 45 years and our struggle has not come to an end yet. We are supporting their government because we realise that their existence depends on us. We will fight all policies that we feel will be anti-people. We will be the force that will control the government.																								The CPM leader admitted to errors in the past. We made some wrong decisions. We also admitted our mistakes. It is possible that the decision taken by our party today may be proved wrong tomorrow.																								We want to utilise the Congress-led Centre as an instrument of struggle... 
